A super fan of actor, Mike Godson has recounted how she almost got scammed by an Instagram user on the app using a picture of the actor. The lady who identified herself as Sarah on an Instagram live disclosed this to the actor and his over 1.4 million fans. Narrating her experience, she said she found out that he was a scammer when he accepted to do a video call.   My plans for Foundation Night, by Ruggedman     Wyze to release Popping Bottles     JAMB denied my ambition to study law, Shan George   Sarah also said the scammer confessed to scamming several of Mike Godson’s fans but commended her saying she was a smart woman. The fan also said the scammer appealed to her not to reveal his antics which she agreed to but noted that she would tell it all to Mike Godson if she had an opportunity to engage him on a video call. “When he found out that I was not going with whatever he wanted he confessed, he told me Sarah you are a very smart woman, for real I am not Mike, this is what I do for a living, I asked him why he said I have been an honest woman please and I should not take him wrong, I just want to tell you the truth and we talked like for two weeks I said okay go ahead but I know the truth and he said that’s why he felt so bad because I wasn’t stupid like other women, he was like he scammed like thousand of Mike’s fans,” Sarah said. Reacting to Sarah’s experience, Godson advised his fans never to fall for scammers using his pictures, in his words “I am very excited that people are beginning to know the truth because these guys are really smart, they follow me here, they lift my picture and my videos to scam other people so I am excited that people are beginning to know the truth and that is a good thing. Just be careful alright, anyone who hit you up knows it is not me I can’t just hit you up, it is impossible I can’t do that.”